obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (44001)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44001&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `This Act may be called the Indian Trusts Act, 1882:`
  line
  line `Commencement.-- and it shall come into force on the first day of March, 1882.`
  line
  line `Local extent.-- ^1[It extends to ^2[the whole of India ^3*** and] the Andaman and Nicobar`
  line `Islands ^4***; but the Central Government may, from time to time, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, extend it to ^5[the, Andaman and Nicobar Islands] or to any part thereof.]`
  line
  line `Savings.-- But nothing herein contained affects the rules of Muhammadan law as to waqf, or the`
  line `mutual relations of the members of an undivided family as determined by any customary or personal`
  line `law, or applies to public or private religious or charitable endowments, or to trusts to distribute`
  line `prizes taken in war among the captors; and nothing in the second Chapter of this Act applies to`
  line `trusts created before the said day.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1948, for the first sentence.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for all the Provinces of India, except.`
  line
  line `3. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 31-10-`
  line `2019).`
  line
  line `4. The words "and Panth Piploda" omitted by the A.O. 1950.`
  line
  line `5. Subs., ibid., for either or both of the said provinces.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (44002)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Repeal of enactments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44002&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `The Statute and Acts mentioned in the Schedule hereto annexed shall, to`
  line `the extent mentioned in the said Schedule, be repealed, in the territories to which this Act for the time`
  line `being extends.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (44003)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Interpretation-clause.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44003&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `A "trust":-- is an obligation annexed to the ownership of`
  line `property, and arising out of a confidence reposed in and accepted by the owner, or declared and accepted`
  line `by him, for the benefit of another, or of another and the owner:`
  line
  line `"author of the trust": "trustee": "beneficiary": "trust-property": "beneficial interest":`
  line `"instrument of trust":-- "the person who reposes or declares the confidence is called the "author of the`
  line `trust": the person who accepts the confidence is called the trustee: the person for whose benefit the`
  line `confidence is accepted is called the "beneficiary": the subject-matter of the trust is called "trust-property"`
  line `or "trust-money": the "beneficial interest" or "interest" of the beneficiary is his right against the trustee`
  line `as owner of the trust-property; and the instrument, if any, by which the trust is declared is called the`
  line `"instrument of trust":`
  line
  line `"breach of trust":-- "a breach of any duty imposed on a trustee, as such, by any law for the time`
  line `being in force, is called a "breach of trust":`
  line
  line `"registered" :"and in this Act, unless there be something repugnant in the subject or context,`
  line `registered" means registered under the law for the registration of documents for the time being in force:`
  line
  line `"notice": "a person is said to have notice of a fact either when he actually knows that fact or`
  line `when, but for wilful abstention from inquiry or gross negligence, he would have known it, or when`
  line `information of the fact is given to or obtained by his agent, under the circumstances mentioned in the`
  line `Indian Contract Act, 1872 (9 of 1872), section 229;`
  line
  line `Expressions defined in Act 9 of 1872:--and all expressions used herein and defined in the Indian`
  line `Contract Act, 1872 (9 of 1872), shall be deemed to have the meanings respectively attributed to them by`
  line `that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (44004)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Lawful purpose.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44004&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `A trust may be created for any lawful purpose. The purpose of a trust is`
  line `lawful unless it is (a) forbidden by law, or (b) is of such a nature that, if permitted, it would`
  line `defeat the provisions of any law, or (c) is fraudulent, or (d) involves or implies injury to the`
  line `person or property of another, or (e) the Court regards it as immoral or opposed to public policy.`
  line
  line `Every trust of which the purpose is unlawful is void. And where a trust is created for two purposes, of`
  line `which one is lawful and the other unlawful, and the two purposes cannot be separated, the whole trust is`
  line void.
  line
  line `Explanation.-- In this section, the expression law includes, where the trust-property is immoveable`
  line `and situate in a foreign country, the law of such country.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A conveys property to B in trust to apply the profits to the nurture of female foundlings to be trained up as prostitutes.`
  line `The trust is void.`
  line
  line `(b) A bequeaths property to B in trust to employ it in carrying on a smuggling business, and out of the profits thereof to`
  line `support A's children. The trust is void.`
  line
  line `(c) A, while in insolvent circumstances, transfers property to B in trust for A during his life, and after his death for B. A is`
  line `declared an insolvent. The trust for A is invalid as against his creditors.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (44005)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Trust of immoveable property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44005&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `No trust in relation to immoveable property is valid`
  line `unless declared by a non-testamentary instrument in writing signed by the author of the trust or`
  line `the trustee and registered, or by the will of the author of the trust or of the trustee.`
  line
  line `Trust of moveable property.-- No trust in relation to moveable property is valid unless`
  line `declared as aforesaid, or unless the ownership of the property is transferred to the trustee.`
  line
  line `These rules do not apply where they would operate so as to effectuate a fraud.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (44006)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Creation of trust.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44006&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of section 5, a trust is created when the author of the`
  line `trust indicates with reasonable certainty by any words or acts (a) an intention on his part to create thereby`
  line `a trust, (b) the purpose of the trust, (c) the beneficiary, and (d) the trust-property, and (unless the trust is`
  line `declared by will or the author of the trust is himself to be the trustee) transfers the trust-property to the`
  line trustee.
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A bequeaths certain property to B, having the fullest confidence that he will dispose of it for the benefit of C. This`
  line `creates a trust so far as regards A and C.`
  line
  line `(b) A bequeaths certain property to B, "hoping he will continue it in the family". This does not create a trust, as the`
  line `beneficiary is not indicated with reasonable certainty.`
  line
  line `(c) A bequeaths certain property to B, requesting him to distribute it amongst such members of C's family as B should`
  line `think most deserving. This does not create a trust, for the beneficiaries are not indicated with reasonable certainty.`
  line
  line `(d) A bequeaths certain property to B, desiring him to divide the bulk of it among C's children. This does not create a trust,`
  line `for the trust-property is not indicated with sufficient certainty.`
  line
  line `(e) A bequeaths a shop and stock-in-trade to B, on condition that he pays As debts and a legacy to C. This is a condition,`
  line `not a trust for As creditors and C.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (44007)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Who may create trusts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes `1 . See s.11 of the Indian Contract Act, 1872 (9 of 1872).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44007&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `A trust may be created--`
  line
  line `(a) by every person competent to contracts ^1, and`
  line
  line `(b) with the permission of a principal Civil Court of original jurisdiction, by or on behalf of a`
  line `minor; but subject in each case to the law for the time being in force as to the`
  line `circumstances and extent in and to which the author of the trust may dispose of the trustproperty.`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (44008)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Subject of trust.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44008&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The subject-matter of a trust must be property transferable to the`
  line beneficiary.
  line
  line `It must not be a merely beneficial interest under a subsisting trust.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (44009)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Who may be beneficiary.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44009&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Every person capable of holding property may be a`
  line beneficiary.
  line
  line `Disclaimer by beneficiary.--A proposed beneficiary may renounce his interest under the`
  line `trust by disclaimer addressed to the trustee, or by setting up, with notice of the trust, a claim`
  line `inconsistent therewith.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (44010)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Who may be trustee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44010&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Every person capable of holding property may be a trustee; but,`
  line `where the trust involves the exercise of discretion, he cannot execute it unless he is competent to`
  line contract.
  line
  line `No one bound to accept trust.-- No one is bound to accept a trust.`
  line
  line `Acceptance of trust.-- A trust is accepted by any words or acts of the trustee indicating with`
  line `reasonable certainty such acceptance.`
  line
  line `Disclaimer of trust.-- Instead of accepting a trust, the intended trustee may, within a`
  line `reasonable period, disclaim it, and such disclaimer shall prevent the trust-property from`
  line `vesting in him.`
  line
  line `A disclaimer by one of two or more co-trustees vests the trust-property in the other or`
  line `others, and makes him or them sole trustee or trustees from the date of the creation of the trust.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A bequeaths certain property to B and C, his executors, as trustees for D. B and C prove A's will. This is in itself an`
  line `acceptance of the trust, and B and C hold the property in trust for D.`
  line
  line `(b) A transfers certain property to B in trust to sell it and to pay out of the proceeds A's debts. B accepts the trust and sells`
  line `the property. So far as regards B, a trust of the proceeds is created for A's creditors.`
  line
  line `(c) A bequeaths a lakh of rupees to B upon certain trusts and appoints him his executor. B severs the lakh from the general`
  line `assets and appropriates it to the specific purpose. This is an acceptance of the trust.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (44011)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Trustee to execute trust.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44011&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The trustee is bound to fulfil the purpose of the trust, and to`
  line `obey the directions of the author of the trust given at the time of its creation, except as modified`
  line `by the consent of all the beneficiaries being competent to contract.`
  line
  line `Where the beneficiary is incompetent to contract, his consent may, for the purposes of this`
  line `section, be given by a principal Civil Court of original jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `Nothing in this section shall be deemed to require a trustee to obey any direction when to`
  line `do so would be impracticable, illegal or manifestly injurious to the beneficiaries.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- Unless a contrary intention be expressed, the purpose of a trust for the`
  line `payment of debts shall be deemed to be (a) to pay only the debts of the author of the trust`
  line `existing and recoverable at the date of the instrument of trust, or, when such instrument is a`
  line `will, at the date of his death, and (b) in the case of debts not bearing interest, to make such`
  line `payment without interest.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A, a trustee, is simply authorised to sell certain land by public auction. He cannot sell the land by private contract.`
  line
  line `(b) A, a trustee of certain land for X, Y and Z, is authorised to sell the land to B for a specified sum. X, Y and Z, being`
  line `competent to contract, consent that A may sell the land to C for a less sum. A may sell the land accordingly.`
  line
  line `(c) A, a trustee for B and her children, is directed by the author of the trust to lend, on B's request, trust-property to Bs`
  line `husband, C, on the security of his bond. C becomes insolvent and B requests A to make the loan. A may refuse to make it.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (44012)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Trustee to inform himself of state of trust-property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44012&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `A trustee is bound to acquaint`
  line `himself, as soon as possible, with the nature and circumstances of the trust-property; to obtain,`
  line `where necessary, a transfer of the trust-property to himself; and (subject to the provisions of the`
  line `instrument of trust) to get in trust-moneys invested on insufficient or hazardous security.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) The trust-property is a debt outstanding on personal security. The instrument of trust gives the trustee no discretionary`
  line `power to leave the debt so outstanding. The trustees duty is to recover the debt without unnecessary`
  line delay.
  line
  line `(b) The trust-property is money in the hands of one of two co-trustees. No discretionary power is given by the instrument of`
  line `trust. The other co-trustee must not allow the former to retain the money for a longer period than the circumstances of the case`
  line required.
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (44013)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Trustee to protect title to trust-property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `1 See now the Indian Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44013&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `A trustee is bound to maintain and defend`
  line `all such suits, and (subject to the provisions of the instrument of trust) to take such other steps`
  line `as, regard being had to the nature and amount or value of the trust-property, may be reasonably`
  line `requisite for the preservation of the trust-property and the assertion or protection of the title`
  line thereto.
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `The trust-property is immoveable property which has been given to the author of the trust by an unregistered instrument.`
  line `Subject to the provisions of the Indian Registration Act, 1877^1 (3 of 1877), the trustees duty is to cause the instrument to be`
  line registered.
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (44014)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Trustee not to set up title adverse to beneficiary.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44014&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The trustee must not for himself`
  line `or another set-up or aid any title to the trust-property adverse to the interest of the beneficiary.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (44015)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Care required from trustee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44015&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `A trustee is bound to deal with the trust-property as`
  line `carefully as a man of ordinary prudence would deal with such property if it were his own; and, in the`
  line `absence of a contract to the contrary, a trustee so dealing is not responsible for the loss, destruction or`
  line `deterioration of the trust-property.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A, living in Calcutta, is a trustee for B, living in Bombay. A remits trust-funds to B by bills drawn by a`
  line `person of undoubted credit in favour of the trustee as such, and payable at Bombay. The bills are dishonoured. A is`
  line `not bound to make good the loss.`
  line
  line `(b) A, a trustee of leasehold property, directs the tenant to pay the rents on account of the trust to a banker, B, then`
  line `in credit. The rents are accordingly paid to B, and A !eaves the money with B only till wanted. Before the money is`
  line `drawn out, B becomes insolvent. A, having had no reason to believe that B was in insolvent circumstances, is not bound`
  line `to make good the loss.`
  line
  line `(c) A, a trustee of two debts for B, releases one and compounds the other, in good faith, and reasonably`
  line `believing that it is for B's interest to do so. A is not bound to make good any loss caused thereby to B.`
  line
  line `(d) A, a trustee directed to sell the trust-property by auction, sells the same, hut does not advertise the sale and`
  line `otherwise fails in reasonable diligence in inviting competition. A is bound to make good the loss caused thereby to the`
  line beneficiary.
  line
  line `(e) A, a trustee for B, in execution of his trust, sells the trust-property, but from want of due diligence on his`
  line `part fails to receive part of the purchase-money. A is bound to make good the loss thereby caused to B.`
  line
  line `(f) A, a trustee for B of a policy of insurance, has funds in hand for payment of the premiums. A neglects to`
  line `pay the premiums, and the policy is consequently forfeited. A is bound to make good the loss to B.`
  line
  line `(g) A bequeaths certain moneys to B and C as trustees, and authorises them to continue trust-moneys upon the`
  line `personal security of a certain firm in which A had himself invested them. A dies, and a change takes place in the`
  line `firm. B and C must not permit the moneys to remain upon the personal security of the new firm.`
  line
  line `(h) A, a trustee for B, allows the trust to be executed solely by his co-trustee, C. C misapplies the trust-property. A is`
  line `personally answerable for the loss resulting to B.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (44016)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Conversion of perishable property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44016&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Where the trust is created for the benefit of several`
  line `persons in succession, and the trust-property is of a wasting nature or a future or reversionary`
  line `interest, the trustee is bound, unless an intention to the contrary may be inferred from the`
  line `instrument of trust, to convert the property into property of a permanent and immediately profitable`
  line character.
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A bequeaths to B all his property in trust for C during his life, and on his death for D, and on D's death`
  line `for E. A's property consists of three leasehold houses, and there is nothing in As will to show that he intended the`
  line `houses to be enjoyed in specie. B should sell the houses, and invest the proceeds in accordance with section 20.`
  line
  line `(b) A bequeaths to B his three leasehold houses in Calcutta and all the furniture therein in trust for C during his`
  line `life, and on his death for D, and on D's death for E. Here an intention that the houses and furniture should be`
  line `enjoyed in specie appears clearly, and B should not sell them.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (44017)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Trustee to be impartial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44017&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Where there are more beneficiaries than one, the trustee is bound`
  line `to be impartial, and must not execute the trust for the advantage of one at the expense of another.`
  line `Where the trustee has a discretionary power, nothing in this section sha ll be deemed to`
  line `authorize the Court to control the exercise reasonably and in good faith of such discretion.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `A, a trustee for B, C and D, is empowered to choose between several specified modes of investing the trust -`
  line `property. A in good faith chooses one of these modes. The Court will not interfere, although the result of the`
  line `choice may be to vary the relative rights of B, C and D.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (44018)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Trustee to prevent waste.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44018&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Where the trust is created for the benefit of several persons in`
  line `succession and one of them is in possession of the trust-property, if he commits, or threatens to commit,`
  line `any act which is destructive or permanently injurious thereto, the trustee is bound to take measures to`
  line `prevent such act.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (44019)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Accounts and information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44019&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `A trustee is bound (a) to keep clear and accurate accounts of the`
  line `trust- property, and (b), at all reasonable times, at the request of the beneficiary, to furnish him with full`
  line `and accurate information as to the amount and state of the trust-property.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (44020)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Investment of trust-money.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 34 of 2016, s. 2, for section 20 (w.e.f. 17-4-2017).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44020&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `^1[20. Investment of trust-money.--Where the trust-property consists of money and cannot be`
  line `applied immediately or at an early date to the purposes of the trust, the trustee shall, subject to any`
  line `direction contained in the instrument of trust, invest the money in any of the securities or class of`
  line `securities expressly authorised by the instrument of trust or as specified by the Central`
  line `Government, by notification in the Official Gazette:`
  line
  line `Provided that where there is a person competent to contract and entitled in possession to`
  line `receive the income of the trust-property for his life, or for any greater estate, no investment in any of the securities or class of securities mentioned above shall be made without his`
  line `consent in writing.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, the expression “securities” shall have the`
  line `same meaning as assigned to it in clause (h) of section 2 of the Securities Contracts`
  line `(Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956).]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_a:
  sectionId (44021)
  sectionNo 20A
  orderNo 21
  title `Power to purchase redeemable stock at a premium.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44021&sectionno=20A&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_20_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[20A. Power to purchase redeemable stock at a premium.--(1) A trustee may invest in any of the`
  line `securities mentioned or referred to in section 20, notwithstanding that the same may be redeemable and`
  line `that the price exceeds the redemption value:`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `(2) A trustee may retain until redemption any redeemable stock, fund or security which may have`
  line `been purchased in accordance with this section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 1916, s. 3.`
  line
  line `2. The proviso omitted by Act 34 of 2016, s. 3 (w.e.f. 17-4-2017).`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (44022)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 22
  title `Mortgage of land pledged to Government under Act 26 of 1871.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes `1 See now the Land Improvement Loans Act, 1883 (19 of 1883).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44022&sectionno=21&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in section 20 shall apply to investments made before this Act comes into`
  line `force, or shall be deemed to preclude an investment on a mortgage of immoveable property already`
  line `pledged as security for an advance under the Land Improvement Act, 1871^1, or, in case the trustmoney does not exceed three thousand rupees, a deposit thereof in a Government Savings Bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (44023)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 23
  title `Sale by trustee directed to sell within specified time.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44023&sectionno=22&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Where a trustee directed to sell within a`
  line `specified time extends such time, the burden of proving, as between himself and the beneficiary, that the`
  line `latter is not prejudiced by the extension lies upon the trustee, unless the extension has been authorised by`
  line `a principal Civil Court of original jurisdiction.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `A bequeaths property to B, directing him with all convenient speed and within five years to sell it, and apply the proceeds`
  line `for the benefit of C. In the exercise of reasonable discretion, B postpones the sale for six years. The sale is not thereby rendered`
  line `invalid, but C, alleging that he has been injured by the postponement, institutes a suit against B to obtain compensation. In such`
  line `suit the burden of proving that C has not been injured lies on B.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (44024)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 24
  title `Liability for breach of trust.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44024&sectionno=23&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Where the trustee commits a breach of trust, he is liable to`
  line `make good the loss which the trust-property or the beneficiary has thereby sustained, unless the`
  line `beneficiary has by fraud induced the trustee to commit the breach, or the beneficiary, being`
  line `competent to contract, has himself, without coercion or undue influence having been brought to bear`
  line `on him, concurred in the breach, or subsequently acquiesced therein, with full knowledge of the`
  line `facts of the case and of his rights as against the trustee.`
  line
  line `A trustee committing a breach of trust is not liable to pay interest except in the following cases:--`
  line
  line `(a) where he has actually received interest;`
  line
  line `(b) where the breach consists in unreasonable delay in paying trust-money to the beneficiary;`
  line
  line `(c) where the trustee ought to have received interest, but has not done so;`
  line
  line `(d) where he may be fairly presumed to have received interest;`
  line
  line `He is liable, in case (a), to account for the interest actually received, and, in cases (b), (c) and`
  line
  line `(d), to account for simple interest at the rate of six per cent. per annum, unless the Court otherwise`
  line directs.
  line
  line `(e) where the breach consists in failure to invest trust-money and to accumulate the interest or`
  line `dividends thereon, he is liable to account for compound interest (with half-yearly rests) at the same`
  line rate;
  line
  line `(f) where the breach consists in the employment of trust-property or the proceeds thereof in`
  line `trade or business, he is liable to account, at the option of the beneficiary, either for compound`
  line `interest (with half-yearly rests) at the same rate, or for the net profits made by such employment`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A trustee improperly leaves trust-property outstanding, and it is consequently lost: he is liable to make good the property`
  line `lost, but he is not liable to pay interest thereon.`
  line
  line `(b) A bequeaths a house to B in trust to sell it and pay the proceeds to C. B neglects to sell the house for a great length of`
  line `time, whereby the house is deteriorated and its market-price falls. B is answerable to C for the loss.`
  line
  line `(c) A trustee is guilty of unreasonable delay in investing trust-money in accordance with section 20, or in paying it to the`
  line `beneficiary. The trustee is liable to pay interest thereon for the period of the delay.`
  line
  line `(d) The duty of the trustee is to invest trust-money in any of the securities mentioned in section 20, clause (a), (b), (c) or (d).`
  line `Instead of so doing, he retains the money in his hands. He is liable, at the option of the beneficiary, to be charged either with the`
  line `amount of the principal money and interest, or with the amount of such securities as he might have purchased with the trustmoney when the investment should have been made, and the intermediate dividends and interest thereon.`
  line
  line `(e) The instrument of trust directs the trustee to invest trust-money either in any of such securities or on mortgage of`
  line `immoveable property. The trustee does neither. He is liable for the principal money and interest.`
  line
  line `(f) The instrument of trust directs the trustee to invest trust-money in any of such securities and to accumulate the dividends`
  line `thereon. The trustee disregards the direction. He is liable, at the option of the beneficiary, to be charged either with the amount of`
  line `the principal money and compound interest, or with the amount of such securities as he might have purchased with the trustmoney when the investment should have been made, together with the amount of the accumulation which would have arisen from`
  line `a proper investment of the intermediate devidends.`
  line
  line `(g) Trust-property is invested in one of the securities mentioned in section 20, clause (a), (b), (c) or (d). The trustee sells`
  line `such security for some purpose not authorised by the terms of the instrument of trust. He is liable, at the option of the beneficiary,`
  line `either to replace the security with the intermediate dividends and interest thereon, or to account for the proceeds of the sale with`
  line `interest thereon.`
  line
  line `(h) The trust-property consists of land. The trustee sells the land to a purchaser for a consideration without notice of the`
  line `trust. The trustee is liable, at the option of the beneficiary, to purchase other land of equal value to be settled upon the like trust,`
  line `or to be charged with the proceeds of the sale with interest.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (44025)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 25
  title `No set-off allowed to trustee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44025&sectionno=24&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `A trustee who is liable for a loss occasioned by a`
  line `breach of trust in respect of one portion of the trust-property cannot set-off against his`
  line `liability a gain which has accrued to another portion of the trust-property through another`
  line `and distinct breach of trust.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (44026)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 26
  title `Non-liability for predecessor’s default.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44026&sectionno=25&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Where a trustee succeeds another, he is not, as such,`
  line `liable for the acts or defaults of his predecessor.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (44027)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 27
  title `Non-liability for co-trustee’s default.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44027&sectionno=26&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of sections 13 and`
  line `15, one trustee is not, as such, liable for a breach of trust committed by his co -trustee:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in the absence of an express declaration to the contrary in the instrument of trust, a`
  line `trustee is so liable--`
  line
  line `(a) where he has delivered trust-property to his co-trustee without seeing to its proper`
  line application;
  line
  line `(b) where he allows his co-trustee to receive trust-property and fails to make due`
  line `enquiry as to the co-trustee's dealings therewith, or allows him to retain it longer than the`
  line `circumstances of the case reasonably require;`
  line
  line `(c) where he becomes aware of a breach of trust committed or intended by his co-trustee, and`
  line `either actively conceals it or does not within a reasonable time take proper steps to protect the`
  line `beneficiary's interest.`
  line
  line `Joining in receipt for conformity.-- A co-trustee who joins in signing a receipt for trustproperty and proves that he has not received the same is not answerable, by reason of such`
  line `signature only, for loss or misapplication of the property by his co-trustee.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `A bequeaths certain property to B and C, and directs .`
  line `ahem to sell it and invest the proceeds for the benefit of D.`
  line `B and C accordingly sell the property, and the purchase-money is received by B and retained in his hands. C pays no`
  line `attention to the matter for two years and then calls on B to make the investment. B is unable to do so, becomes`
  line `insolvent, and the purchase-money is lost. C may be compelled to make good the amount.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (44028)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 28
  title `Several liability of co-trustees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44028&sectionno=27&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `Where co-trustees jointly commit a breach of trust,`
  line `or where one of them by his neglect enables the other to commit a breach of trust, each is`
  line `liable to the beneficiary for the whole of the loss occasioned by such breach.`
  line
  line `Contribution as between co-trustees.-- But as between the trustees themselves, if one be`
  line `less guilty than another and has had to refund the loss, the former may compel the latter, or`
  line `his legal representative to the extent of the assets he has received, to make good such loss;`
  line `and if all be equally guilty, any one or more of the trustees who has had to refund the loss`
  line `may compel the others to contribute.`
  line
  line `Nothing in this section shall be deemed to authorise a trustee who has been guilty of`
  line `fraud to institute a suit to compel contribution.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (44029)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 29
  title `Non-liability of trustee paying without notice of transfer by beneficiary.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44029&sectionno=28&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line When
  line `any beneficiary's interest becomes vested in another person, and the trustee, not having notice`
  line `of the vesting, pays or delivers trust-property to the person who would have been entitled`
  line `thereto in the absence of such vesting, the trustee is not liable for the property so paid or`
  line delivered.
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (44030)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 30
  title `Liability of trustee where beneficiary’s interest is forfeited to the Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44030&sectionno=29&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `When the`
  line `beneficiary's interest is forfeited or awarded by legal adjudication ^1[to the Government], the trustee is`
  line `bound to hold the trust-property to the extent of such interest for the benefit of such person in such`
  line `manner as ^2the State Government may direct in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 The words "to Government" successively amended by the A.O. 1937 and the A.O. 1950, to read as above.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "the Government".`
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (44031)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 31
  title `Indemnity of trustees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44031&sectionno=30&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of the instrument of trust and of`
  line `sections 23 and 26, trustees shall be respectively chargeable only for such moneys, stocks,`
  line `funds and securities as they respectively actually receive, and shall not be answerable the one`
  line `for the other of them, nor for any banker, broker or other person in whose hands any trust -`
  line `property may be placed, nor for the insufficiency or deficiency of any stocks, funds or`
  line `securities, nor otherwise for involuntary losses.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (44032)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 32
  title `Right to title-deed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44032&sectionno=31&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `A trustee is entitled to have in his possession the instrument of trust and all`
  line `the documents of title (if any) relating solely to the trust-property`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (44033)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 33
  title `Right to reimbursement of expenses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44033&sectionno=32&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Every trustee may reimburse himself, or pay`
  line `or discharge out of the trust-property, all expenses properly incurred in or about the execution`
  line `of the trust, or the realisation, preservation or benefit of the trust-property, or the protection`
  line `or support of the beneficiary.`
  line
  line `If he pays such expenses out of his own pocket he has a first charge upon the trust-property`
  line `for such expenses and interest thereon; but such charge (unless the expenses have been incurred`
  line `with the sanction of a principal Civil Court of original jurisdiction) shall be enforced only by`
  line `prohibiting and disposition of the trust-property without previous payment of such expenses and`
  line interest.
  line
  line `If the trust-property fail, the trustee is entitled to recover from the beneficiary personally`
  line `on whose behalf he acted, and at whose request, expressed or implied, he made the payment,`
  line `the amount of such expenses.`
  line
  line `Right to be recouped for erroneous over-payment.-- Where a trustee has by mistake made`
  line `an over-payment to the beneficiary, he may reimburse the trust-property out of the beneficiary's`
  line `interest. If such interest fail, the trustee is entitled to recover from the beneficiary personally the`
  line `amount of such over-payment.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (44034)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 34
  title `Right to indemnity from gainer by breach of trust.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44034&sectionno=33&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `A person other than a trustee`
  line `who has gained an advantage from a breach of trust must indemnify the trustee to the extent`
  line `of the amount actually received by such person under the breach; and where he is a`
  line `beneficiary the trustee has a charge on his interest for such amount.`
  line
  line `Nothing in this section shall be deemed to entitle a trustee to be indemnified who has, in committing`
  line `the breach of trust, been guilty of fraud.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (44035)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 35
  title `Right to apply to Court for opinion in management of trust -property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44035&sectionno=34&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Any trustee`
  line `may, without instituting a suit, apply by petition to a principal Civil Court of original`
  line `jurisdiction for its opinion, advice or direction on any present questions respecting the`
  line `management or administration of the trust-property other than questions of detail, difficulty or`
  line `importance, not proper in the opinion of the Court for summary disposal.`
  line
  line `A copy of such petition shall be served upon, and the hearing thereof may be attended by,`
  line `such of the persons interested in the application as the Court thinks fit.`
  line
  line `The trustee stating in good faith the facts in such petition and acting upon the opinion, advice`
  line `or direction given by the Court shall be deemed, so far as regards his own responsibility, to have`
  line `discharged his duty as such trustee in the subject-matter of the application.`
  line
  line `The costs of every application under this section shall be in the discretion of the Court to which it is`
  line made.
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (44036)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 36
  title `Right to settlement of accounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44036&sectionno=35&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `When the duties of a trustee, as such, are completed,`
  line `he is entitled to have the accounts of his administration of the trust-property examined and settled;`
  line `and, where nothing is due to the beneficiary under the trust, to an acknowledgment in writing to`
  line `that effect.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (44037)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 37
  title `General authority of trustee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes `1 Second paragraph rep. by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and the First Schedule.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44037&sectionno=36&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `In addition to the powers expressly conferred by this`
  line `Act and by the instrument of trust, and subject to the restrictions, if any, contained in such`
  line `instrument, and to the provisions of section 17, a trustee may do all acts which are reasonable`
  line `and proper for the realisation, protection or benefit of the trust-property, and for the protection`
  line `or support of a beneficiary who is not competent to contract.`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `Except with the permission of a principal Civil Court of original jurisdiction, no trustee shall`
  line `lease trust-property for a term exceeding twenty-one years from the date of executing the lease,`
  line `nor without reserving the best yearly rent that can be reasonably obtained.`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (44038)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 38
  title `Power to sell in lots, and either by public auction or private contract.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44038&sectionno=37&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `Where the`
  line `trustee is empowered to sell any trust-property, he may sell the same subject to prior charges or`
  line `not, and either together or in lots, by public auction or private contract, and either at one time or`
  line `at several times, unless the instrument of trust otherwise direc ts.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (44039)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 39
  title `Power to sell under special conditions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44039&sectionno=38&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `The trustee`
  line `making any such sale may insert such reasonable stipulations either as to title or evidence of title,`
  line `or otherwise, in any conditions of sale or contract for sale, as he thinks fit; and may also buy-in`
  line `the property or any part thereof at any sale by auction, and rescind or vary any contract for sale, and re-sell the property so bought in, or as to which the contract is so rescinded, without being`
  line `responsible to the beneficiary for any loss occasioned thereby.`
  line
  line `Time allowed for selling trust-property.-- Where a trustee is directed to sell trust-property or to`
  line `invest trust-money in the purchase of property, he may exercise a reasonable discretion as to the time of`
  line `effecting the sale or purchase.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A bequeaths property to B, directing him to sell it with all convenient speed and pay the proceeds to C. This does not`
  line `render an immediate sale imperative.`
  line
  line `(b) A bequeaths property to B, directing him to sell it at such time and in such manner as he shall think fit and`
  line `invest the proceeds for the benefit of C. This does not authorise B, as between him and C, to postpone the sale to an`
  line `indefinite period.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (44040)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 40
  title `Power to convey.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44040&sectionno=39&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of completing any such sale, the trustee shall have power to`
  line `convey or otherwise dispose of the property sold in such manner as may be necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (44041)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 41
  title `Power to vary investments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44041&sectionno=40&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `A trustee may, at his discretion, call in any trust-property`
  line `invested in any security and invest the same on any of the securities mentioned or referred to in`
  line `section 20, and from time to time vary any such investments for others of the same nature:`
  line
  line `Provided that, where there is a person competent to contract and entitled at the time to`
  line `receive the income of the trust-property for his life, or for any greater estate, no such change of`
  line `investment shall be made without his consent in writing.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (44042)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 42
  title `Power to apply property of minors, etc., for their maintenance, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44042&sectionno=41&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `Where any`
  line `property is held by a trustee in trust for a minor, such trustee may, at his discretion, pay to the`
  line `guardians (if any) of such minor, or otherwise apply for or towards his maintenance or education`
  line `or advancement in life, or the reasonable expenses of his religious worship, marriage or funeral,`
  line `the whole or any part of the income to which he may be entitled in respect of such property; and such`
  line `trustee shall accumulate all the residue of such income by way of compound interest, by investing the`
  line `same and the resulting income thereof from time to time in any of the securities mentioned or referred to`
  line `in section 20, for the benefit of the person who shall ultimately become entitled to the property from`
  line `which such accumulations have arisen: Provided that such trustee may, at any time, if he thinks fit, apply`
  line `the whole or any part of such accumulations as if the same were part of the income arising in the then`
  line `current year.`
  line
  line `Where the income of the trust-property is insufficient for the minors maintenance or education or`
  line `advancement in life, or the reasonable expenses of his religious worship, marriage or funeral, the trustee`
  line `may, with the permission of a principal Civil Court of original jurisdiction, but not otherwise, apply the`
  line `whole or any part of such property for or towards such maintenance, education, advancement or expenses.`
  line
  line `Nothing in this section shall be deemed to affect the provisions of any local law for the time being in`
  line `force relating to the persons and property of minors.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (44043)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 43
  title `Power to give receipts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44043&sectionno=42&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `Any trustees or trustee may give a receipt in writing for any`
  line `money, securities or other moveable property payable, transferable or deliverable to them or him`
  line `by reason, or in the exercise, of any trust or power; and, in the absence of fraud, such receipt shall`
  line `discharge the person paying, transferring or delivering the same therefrom, and from seeing to the`
  line `application thereof, or being accountable for any loss or misapplication thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (44044)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 44
  title `Power to compound, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44044&sectionno=43&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `Two or more trustees acting together may, if and as they think fit--`
  line
  line `(a) accept any composition or any security for any debt or for any property claimed;`
  line
  line `(b) allow any time for payment of any debt;`
  line
  line `(c) compromise, compound, abandon, submit to arbitration or otherwise settle any debt, account,`
  line `claim or thing whatever relating to the trust; and`
  line
  line `(d) for any of those purposes, enter into, give, execute and do such agreements, instruments`
  line `of composition or arrangement, releases and other things as to them seem expedient, without`
  line `being responsible for any loss occasioned by any act or thing so done by them in good faith.`
  line
  line `The powers conferred by this section on two or more trustees acting together may be`
  line `exercised by a sole acting trustee when by the instrument of trust, if any, a sole trustee is`
  line `authorized to execute the trusts and powers thereof.`
  line
  line `This section applies only if and as far as a contrary intention is not expressed in the`
  line `instrument of trust, if any, and shall have effect subject to the terms of that instrument and to the`
  line `provisions therein contained.`
  line
  line `This section applies only to trusts created after this Act comes into force.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (44045)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 45
  title `Power to several trustees of whom one disclaims or dies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44045&sectionno=44&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `When an authority to deal`
  line `with the trust-property is given to several trustees and one of them disclaims or dies, the authority`
  line `may be exercised by the continuing trustees, unless from the terms of the instrument of trust it is`
  line `apparent that the authority is to be exercised by a number in excess of the number of the remaining`
  line trustees.
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (44046)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 46
  title `Suspension of trustee’s powers by decree.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44046&sectionno=45&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `Where a decree has been made in a suit`
  line `for the execution of a trust, the trustee must not exercise any of his powers except in conformity with such`
  line `decree, or with the sanction of the Court by which the decree has been made, or, where an appeal against`
  line `the decree is pending, of the Appellate Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (44047)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 47
  title `Trustee cannot renounce after acceptance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44047&sectionno=46&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `A trustee who has accepted`
  line `the trust cannot afterwards renounce it except (a) with the permission of a principal`
  line `Civil Court of original jurisdiction, or (b) if the beneficiary is competent to`
  line `contract, with his consent, or ( c) by virtue of a special power in the instrument of`
  line trust.
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (44048)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 48
  title `Trustee cannot delegate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44048&sectionno=47&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `A trustee cannot delegate his office or any of his`
  line `duties either to a co-trustee or to a stranger, unless (a) the instrument of trust so`
  line `provides, or (b) the delegation is in the regular course of business, or (c) the delegation`
  line `is necessary, or (d) the beneficiary, being competent to contract, consents to the`
  line delegation.
  line
  line `Explanation.-- The appointment of an attorney or proxy to do an act merely`
  line `ministerial and involving no independent discretion is not a delegation within the`
  line `meaning of this section.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A bequeaths certain property to B and C on certain trusts to be executed by them or the survivor of them`
  line `or the assigns of such survivor. B dies. C may bequeath the trust-property to D and E upon the trusts of A's will.`
  line
  line `(b) A is a trustee of certain property with power to sell the same. A may employ an auctioneer to effect the`
  line sale.
  line
  line `(c) A bequeaths to B fifty houses let at monthly rents in trust to collect the rents and pay them to C. B may employ a proper`
  line `person to collect these rents.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (44049)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 49
  title `Co-trustees cannot act singly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44049&sectionno=48&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `When there are more trustees than one, all`
  line `must join in the execution of the trust, except where the instrument of trust otherwise`
  line provides.
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (44050)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 50
  title `Control of discretionary power.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44050&sectionno=49&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `Where a discretionary power conferred on a`
  line `trustee is not exercised reasonably and in good faith, such power may be controlled by a`
  line `principal Civil Court of original jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (44051)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 51
  title `Trustee may not charge for services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44051&sectionno=50&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `In the absence of express directions`
  line `to the contrary contained in the instrument of trust or of a contract to the contrary`
  line `entered into with the beneficiary or the Court at the time of accepting the trust, a`
  line `trustee has no right to remuneration for his trouble, skill and loss of time in`
  line `executing the trust.`
  line
  line `Nothing in this section applies to any Official Trustee, Administrator General, Public`
  line `Curator, or person holding a certificate of administration.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (44052)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 52
  title `Trustee may not use trust-property for his own profit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44052&sectionno=51&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `A trustee may not use`
  line `or deal with the trust-property for his own profit or for any other purpose unconnected`
  line `with the trust.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (44053)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 53
  title `Trustee for sale or his agent may not buy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44053&sectionno=52&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `No trustee whose duty it is to sell`
  line `trust-property, and no agent employed by such trustee for the purpose of the sale, may,`
  line `directly or indirectly, buy the same or any interest therein, on his own account or as`
  line `agent for a third person.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (44054)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 54
  title `Trustee may not buy beneficiary’s interest without permission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44054&sectionno=53&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `No trustee, and no`
  line `person who has recently ceased to be a trustee, may, without the permission of a principal Civil Court of`
  line `original jurisdiction, buy or become mortgagee or lessee of the trust-property or any part thereof; and`
  line `such permission shall not be given unless the proposed purchase, mortgage or lease is manifestly for the`
  line `advantage of the beneficiary.`
  line
  line `Trustee for purchase.-- And no trustee whose duty it is to buy or to obtain a mortgage`
  line `or lease of particular property for the beneficiary may buy it, or any part the reof, or obtain a`
  line `mortgage or lease of it, or any part thereof, for himself.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (44055)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 55
  title `Co-trustees may not lend to one of themselves.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44055&sectionno=54&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `A trustee or co-trustee whose duty it`
  line `is to invest trust-money on mortgage or personal security must not invest it on a mortgage by,`
  line `or on the personal security of, himself or one of his co -trustees.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (44056)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 56
  title `Rights to rents and profits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44056&sectionno=55&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `The beneficiary has, subject to the provisions of the`
  line `instrument of trust, a right to the rents and profits of the trust-property.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (44057)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 57
  title `Right to specific execution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44057&sectionno=56&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `The beneficiary is entitled to have the intention of the`
  line `author of the trust specifically executed to the extent of the beneficiary s interest;`
  line
  line `Right to transfer of possession.-- and, where there is only one beneficiary and he is`
  line `competent to contract, or where there are several beneficiaries and they are competent to`
  line `contract and all of one mind, he or they may require the trustee to transfer the trust -property`
  line `to him or them, or to such person as he or they may direct.`
  line
  line `When property has been transferred or bequeathed for the benefit of a married woman, so`
  line `that she shall not have power to deprive herself of her beneficial interest, nothing in the second`
  line `clause of this section applies to such property during her marriage.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `Certain Government securities are given to trustees upon trust to accumulate the interest until A attains the age of 24, and`
  line `then to transfer the gross amount to him. A on attaining majority may, as the person exclusively interested in the trust-property,`
  line `require the trustees to transfer it immediately to him.`
  line
  line `A bequeaths Rs.10,000 to trustees upon trust to purchase an annuity for B, who has attained his majority and is otherwise`
  line `competent to contract. B may claim the Rs. 10,000.`
  line
  line `A transfers certain property to B and directs him to sell or invest it for the benefit of C, who is competent to contract. C may`
  line `elect to take the property in its original character`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (44058)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 58
  title `Right to inspect and take copies of instrument of trust, accounts, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44058&sectionno=57&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `The beneficiary`
  line `has a right, as against the trustee and all persons claiming under him with notice of the trust, to inspect and take copies of the instrument of trust, the documents of title r elating solely to the`
  line `trust-property, the accounts of the trust-property and the vouchers (if any) by which they are`
  line `supported, and the cases submitted and opinions taken by the trustee for his guidance in the`
  line `discharge of his duty.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (44059)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 59
  title `Right to transfer beneficial interest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44059&sectionno=58&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `The beneficiary, if competent to contract, may`
  line `transfer his interest, but subject to the law for the time being in force as to the circumstances`
  line `and extent in and to which he may dispose of such interest:`
  line
  line `Provided that when property is transferred or bequeathed for the benefit of a married`
  line `woman, so that she shall not have power to deprive herself of her beneficial interest, nothing`
  line `in this section shall authorise her to transfer such interest during her marriage.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (44060)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 60
  title `Right to sue for execution of trust.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44060&sectionno=59&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `Where no trustees are appointed or all the`
  line `trustees die, disclaim or are discharged, or where for any other reason the execution of a`
  line `trust by the trustee is or becomes impracticable, the beneficiary may institute a suit for the execution of`
  line `the trust, and the trust shall, so far as may be possible, be executed by the Court until the appointment of a`
  line `trustee or new trustee.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (44061)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 61
  title `Right to proper trustees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "the provinces".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44061&sectionno=60&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `The beneficiary has a right (subject to the provisions of`
  line `the instrument of trust) that the trust-property shall be properly protected and held and`
  line `administered by proper persons and by a proper number of such persons.`
  line
  line `Explanation I.-- The following are not proper persons within the meaning of this section:--`
  line
  line `A person domiciled abroad: an alien enemy: a person having an interest inconsistent with that of the`
  line `beneficiary: a person in insolvent circumstances; and, unless the personal law of the beneficiary allows`
  line `otherwise, a married woman and a minor.`
  line
  line `Explanation II.--When the administration of the trust involves the receipt and custody of money, the`
  line `number of trustees should be two at least.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A, one of several beneficiaries, proves that B, the trustee, has improperly disposed of part of the trust-property, or that`
  line `the property is in danger from B's being in insolvent circumstances, or that he is incapacitated from acting as trustee. A may`
  line `obtain a receiver of the trust-property.`
  line
  line `(b) A bequeaths certain jewels to B in trust for C. B dies during As lifetime; then A dies. C is entitled to have the property`
  line `conveyed to a trustee for him.`
  line
  line `(c) A conveys certain property to four trustees in trust for B. Three of the trustees die. B may institute a suit to have three`
  line `new trustees appointed in the place of the deceased trustees.`
  line
  line `(d) A conveys certain property to three trustees in trust for B. All the trustees disclaim. B may institute a suit to have three`
  line `trustees appointed in place of the trustees so disclaiming.`
  line
  line `(e) A, a trustee for B, refuses to act, or goes to reside permanently out of ^1`
  line `India, or is declared an insolvent, or compounds`
  line `with his creditors, or suffers a co-trustee to commit a breach of trust. B may institute a suit to have A removed and a new trustee`
  line `appointed in his room.`
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (44062)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 62
  title `Right to compel to any act of duty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44062&sectionno=61&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `The beneficiary has a right that his trustee shall be`
  line `compelled to perform any particular act of his duty as such, and restrained from committing any`
  line `contemplated or probable breach of trust.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A contracts with B to pay him monthly Rs.100 for the benefit of C. B writes and signs a letter declaring that he will hold`
  line `in trust for C the money so to be paid. A fails to pay the money in accordance with his contract. C may compel B on a proper`
  line `indemnity to allow C to sue on the contract in B's name.`
  line
  line `(b) A is trustee of certain land, with a power to sell the same and pay the proceeds to B and C equally. A is about to`
  line `make an improvident sale of the land. B may sue on behalf of himself and C for an injunction to restrain A from making`
  line `the sale.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (44063)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 63
  title `Wrongful purchase by trustee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44063&sectionno=62&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `Where a trustee has wrongfully bought trust-property,`
  line `the beneficiary has a right to have the property declared subject to the trust or retransferred by the`
  line `trustee, if it remains in his hands unsold, or, if it has been bought from him by any person with`
  line `notice of the trust, by such person. But in such case the beneficiary must repay the purchase -money`
  line `paid by the trustee, with interest, and such other expenses (if any) as he has properly incurred in`
  line `the preservation of the property; and the trustee or purchaser must (a) account for the net profits of`
  line `the property, (b) be charged with an occupation-rent, if he has been in actual possession of the`
  line `property, and (c) allow the beneficiary to deduct a proportionate part of the purchase-money if the`
  line `property has been deteriorated by the acts or omissions of the trustee or purchaser.`
  line
  line `Nothing in this section--`
  line
  line `(a) impairs the rights of lessees and others who, before the institution of a suit to have the`
  line `property declared subject to the trust or retransferred, have contracted in good faith with the trustee or`
  line `purchaser; or`
  line
  line `(b) entitles the beneficiary to have the property declared subject to the trust or retransferred`
  line `where he, being competent to contract, has himself, without coercion or undue influence having been`
  line `brought to bear on him, ratified the sale to the trustee with full knowledge of the facts of the case and`
  line `of his rights as against the trustee.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (44099)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 64
  title `Following trust-property into the hands of third persons; into that into which it has been converted.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44099&sectionno=63&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `Where trust-property comes`
  line `into the hands of a third person inconsistently with the trust, the beneficiary may require him to admit`
  line `formally, or may institute a suit for a declaration, that the property is comprised in the trust.`
  line
  line `into that into which it has been converted.-- Where the trustee has disposed of trust-property`
  line `and the money or other property which he has received therefor can be traced in his hands, or the`
  line `hands of his legal representative or legatee, the beneficiary has, in respect thereof, rights as nearly as`
  line `may be the same as his rights in respect of the original trust-property.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A, a trustee for B of Rs. 10,000, wrongfully invests the Rs. 10,000 in the purchase of certain land. B is entitled to the`
  line land.
  line
  line `(b) A, a trustee, wrongfully purchases land in his own name, partly with his own money, partly with money`
  line `subject to a trust for B. B is entitled to a charge on the land for the amount of the trust-money so misemployed.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (44065)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 65
  title `Saving of rights of certain transferees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44065&sectionno=64&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in section 63 entitles the beneficiary to any`
  line `right in respect of property in the hands of--`
  line
  line `(a) a transferee in good faith for consideration without having notice of the trust, either when the`
  line `purchase-money was paid, or when the conveyance was executed, or`
  line
  line `(b) a transferee for consideration from such a transferee.`
  line
  line `A judgment-creditor of the trustee attaching and purchasing trust-property is not a transferee for`
  line `consideration within the meaning of this section.`
  line
  line `Nothing in section 63 applies to money, currency notes and negotiable instruments in the hands of a`
  line `bona fide holder to whom they have passed in circulation, or shall be deemed to affect the Indian Contract`
  line `Act, 1872 (9 of 1872), section 108, or the liability of a person to whom a debt or charge is transferred.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (44066)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 66
  title `Acquisition by trustee of trust-property wrongfully converted.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44066&sectionno=65&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `Where a trustee wrongfully`
  line `sells or otherwise transfers trust-property and afterwards himself becomes the owner of the property, the`
  line `property again becomes subject to the trust, notwithstanding any want of notice on the part of intervening`
  line `transferees in good faith for consideration.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (44067)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 67
  title `Right in case of blended property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44067&sectionno=66&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `Where the trustee wrongfully mingles the trustproperty with his own, the beneficiary is entitled to a charge on the whole fund for the amount due`
  line `to him.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (44068)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 68
  title `Wrongful employment by partner-trustee of trust property for partnership purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44068&sectionno=67&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `If a partner, being a trustee, wrongfully employs trust-property in the business or on the account of the partnership, no other partner is liable therefor in his personal capacity to the beneficiaries, unless`
  line `he had notice of the breach of trust.`
  line
  line `The partners having such notice are jointly and severally liable for the breach of trust.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A and B are partners. A dies, having bequeathed all his property to B in trust for Z, and appointed B his sole executor. B,`
  line `instead of winding up the affairs of the partnership, retains all the assets in the business. Z may compel him, as partner, to`
  line `account for so much of the profits as are derived from As share of the capital. B is also answerable to Z for the improper`
  line `employment of As assets.`
  line
  line `(b) A, a trader, bequeaths his property to B in trust for C, appoints B his sole executor, and dies. B enters into partnership`
  line `with X and Y in the same trade, and employs A's assets in the partnership-business. B gives an indemnity to X and Y against the`
  line `claims of C. Here X and Y are jointly liable with B to C as having knowingly become parties to the breach of trust committed by`
  line B.
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (44069)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 69
  title `Liability of beneficiary joining in breach of trust.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44069&sectionno=68&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `Where one of several beneficiaries--`
  line
  line `(a) joins in committing breach of trust, or`
  line
  line `(b) knowingly obtains any advantage therefrom, without the consent of the other beneficiaries, or`
  line
  line `(c) becomes aware of a breach of trust committed or intended to be committed, and either`
  line `actually conceals it, or does not within a reasonable time take proper steps to protect the interests of`
  line `the other beneficiaries, or`
  line
  line `(d) has deceived the trustee and thereby induced him to commit a breach of trust,`
  line `the other beneficiaries are entitled to have all his beneficial interest impounded as against him and`
  line `all who claim under him (otherwise than as transferees for consideration without notice of the`
  line `breach) until the loss caused by the breach has been compensated.`
  line
  line `When property has been transferred or bequeathed for the benefit of a married woman, so that`
  line `she shall not have power to deprive herself of her beneficial interest, nothing in this section applies`
  line `to such property during her marriage.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (44070)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 70
  title `Rights and liabilities of beneficiary’s transferee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44070&sectionno=69&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `Every person to whom a beneficiary`
  line `transfers his interest has the rights, and is subject to the liabilities, of the beneficiary in respect of such`
  line `interest at the date of the transfer.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (44071)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 71
  title `Office how vacated.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44071&sectionno=70&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `The office of a trustee is vacated by his death or by his discharge from his`
  line office
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (44072)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 72
  title `Discharge of trustee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44072&sectionno=71&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `A trustee may be discharged from his office only as follows:--`
  line
  line `(a) by the extinction of the trust;`
  line
  line `(b) by the completion of his duties under the trust;`
  line
  line `(c) by such means as may be prescribed by the instrument of trust;`
  line
  line `(d) by appointment under this Act of a new trustee in his place;`
  line
  line `(e) by consent of himself and the beneficiary, or, where there are more beneficiaries than one, all the beneficiaries being competent to contract; or`
  line
  line `(f) by the Court to which a petition for his discharge is presented under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (44073)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 73
  title `Petition to be discharged from trust.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44073&sectionno=72&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding the provisions of section 11,`
  line `every trustee may apply by petition to a principal Civil Court of original jurisdiction to be`
  line `discharged from his office; and if the Court finds that there is sufficient reason for such discharge,`
  line `it may discharge him accordingly, and direct his costs to be paid out of the trust-property. But where there is no such reason, the Court shall not discharge him, unless a proper person can be`
  line `found to take his place`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (44074)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 74
  title `Appointment of new trustees on death, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "the provinces".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44074&sectionno=73&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any person appointed a trustee`
  line `disclaims, or any trustee, either original or substituted, dies, or is for a continuous period of six months`
  line `absent from ^1[India], or leaves ^1[India] for the purpose of residing abroad, or is declared an insolvent, or`
  line `desires to be discharged from the trust, or refuses or becomes, in the opinion of a principal Civil Court of`
  line `original jurisdiction, unfit or personally incapable to act in the trust, or accepts an inconsistent trust, a new`
  line `trustee may be appointed in his place by--`
  line
  line `(a) the person nominated for that purpose by the instrument of trust (if any), or`
  line
  line `(b) if there be no such person, or no such person able and willing to act, the author of the`
  line `trust if he be alive and competent to contract, or the surviving or continuing trustees or trustee`
  line `for the time being, or legal representative of the last surviving and continuing trustee, or (with`
  line `the consent of the Court) the retiring trustees, if they all retire simultaneously, or (with the`
  line `like consent) the last retiring trustee.`
  line
  line `Every such appointment shall be by writing under the hand of the person making it. On an`
  line `appointment of a new trustee the number of trustees may be increased.`
  line
  line `The Official Trustee may, with his consent and by the order of the Court, be appointed under this`
  line `section, in any case in which only one trustee is to be appointed and such trustee is to be the sole trustee.`
  line
  line `The provisions of this section relative to a trustee who is dead include the case of a person nominated`
  line `trustee in a will but dying before the testator, and those relative to a continuing trustee include a refusing`
  line `or retiring trustee if willing to act in the execution of the power.`
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (44075)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 75
  title `Appointment by Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44075&sectionno=74&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any such vacancy or disqualification occurs and it is`
  line `found impracticable to appoint a new trustee under section 73, the beneficiary may, without instituting`
  line `a suit, apply by petition to a principal Civil Court of original jurisdiction for the appointment of a`
  line `trustee or a new trustee, and the Court may appoint a trustee or a new trustee accordingly.`
  line
  line `Rule for selecting new trustees.-- In appointing new trustees, the Court shall have regard (a)`
  line `to the wishes of the author of the trust as expressed in or to be inferred from the instrument of`
  line `trust; (b) to the wishes of the person, if any, empowered to appoint new trustees; (c) to the question`
  line `whether the appointment will promote or impede the execution of the trust; and (d) where there are`
  line `more beneficiaries than one, to the interests of all such beneficiaries.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (44076)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 76
  title `Vesting of trust-property in new trustees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44076&sectionno=75&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any new trustee is appointed under`
  line `section 73 or section 74, all the trust-property for the time being vested in the surviving or continuing`
  line `trustees or trustee, or in the legal representative of any trustee, shall become vested in such new trustee,`
  line `either solely or jointly with the surviving or continuing trustees or trustee, as the case may require.`
  line
  line `Powers of new trustees.-- Every new trustee so appointed, and every trustee appointed by a`
  line `Court either before or after the passing of this Act, shall have the same powers, authorities and`
  line `discretions, and shall in all respects act, as if he had been originally nominated a trustee by the`
  line `author of the trust.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (44077)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 77
  title `Survival of trust.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44077&sectionno=76&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `On the death or discharge of one of several co-trustees, the trust`
  line `survives and the trust-property passes to the others, unless the instrument of trust expressly declares`
  line otherwise.
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (44078)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 78
  title `Trust how extinguished.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44078&sectionno=77&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `A trust is extinguished--`
  line
  line `(a) when its purpose is completely fulfilled; or`
  line
  line `(b) when its purpose becomes unlawful; or`
  line
  line `(c) when the fulfilment of its purpose becomes impossible by destruction of the trust-property or`
  line `otherwise; or`
  line
  line `(d) when the trust, being revocable, is expressly revoked.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (44079)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 79
  title `Revocation of trust.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44079&sectionno=78&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `A trust created by will may be revoked at the pleasure of the testator.`
  line `A trust otherwise created can be revoked only--`
  line
  line `(a) where all the beneficiaries are competent to contract--by their consent;`
  line
  line `(b) where the trust has been declared by a non-testamentary instrument or by word of`
  line `mouth--in exercise of a power of revocation expressly reserved to the author of the trust; or`
  line
  line `(c) where the trust is for the payment of the debts of the author of the trust, and has not been`
  line `communicated to the creditors--at the pleasure of the author of the trust.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `A conveys property to B in trust to sell the same and pay out of the proceeds the claims of A's creditors. A`
  line `reserves no power of revocation. If no communication has been made to the creditors, A may revoke the trust. But if`
  line `the creditors are parties to the arrangement, the trust cannot be revoked without their consent.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (44080)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 80
  title `Revocation not to defeat what trustees have duly done.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44080&sectionno=79&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `No trust can be revoked by the author`
  line `of the trust so as to defeat or prejudice what the trustees may have duly done in execution of the trust.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (44081)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 81
  title `Where obligation in nature of trust is created.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44081&sectionno=80&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `An obligation in the nature of a trust is created`
  line `in the following cases.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (44082)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 82
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44082&sectionno=81&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `[Where is does not appear that transferor intended to dispose of beneficial interest.] Rep. by the`
  line `Benami Transactions (Prohibition) Act, 1988 (45 of 1988), s. 7 (w.e.f. 19-5-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (44083)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 83
  title [Repealed.].
  content `[Transfer to one for consideration paid by another.] Rep. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 19-5-1988).`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44083&sectionno=82&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (44084)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 84
  title `Trust incapable of execution or executed without exhausting trust -property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44084&sectionno=83&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line Where
  line `a trust is incapable of being executed, or where the trust is completely executed without`
  line `exhausting the trust-property, the trustee, in the absence of a direction to the contrary, must hold`
  line `the trust-property, or so much thereof as is unexhausted, for the benefit of the author of the trust`
  line `or his legal representative.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A conveys certain land to B--`
  line
  line `"upon trust", and no trust is declared; or`
  line
  line `"upon trust to be thereafter declared", and no such declaration is ever made; or`
  line
  line `upon trusts that are too vague to be executed; or`
  line
  line `upon trusts that become incapable of taking effect; or`
  line
  line `"in trust for C", and C renounces his interest under the trust.`
  line
  line `In each of these cases B holds the land for the benefit of A.`
  line
  line `(b) A transfers Rs. 10,000 in the four per cents. to B, in trust to pay the interest annually accruing due to C for`
  line `her life. A dies. Then C dies. B holds the fund for the benefit of A's legal representative.`
  line
  line `(c) A conveys land to B upon trust to sell it and apply one moiety of the proceeds for certain charitable purposes,`
  line `and the other for the maintenance of the worship of an idol. B sells the land, but the charitable purposes wholly fail,`
  line `and the maintenance of the worship does not exhaust the second moiety of the pro ceeds. B holds the first moiety and`
  line `the part unapplied of the second moiety for the benefit of A or his legal representative.`
  line
  line `(d) A bequeaths Rs. 10,000 to B, to be laid out in buying land to be conveyed for purposes which either`
  line `wholly or partially fail to take effect. B holds for the benefit of A's legal representative the undisposed of interest in the money or`
  line `land if purchased.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (44085)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 85
  title `Transfer for illegal purpose.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44085&sectionno=84&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `Where the owner of property transfers it to another for an illegal`
  line `purpose and such purpose is not carried into execution, or the transferor is not as guilty as the transferee,`
  line `or the effect of permitting the transferee to retain the property might be to defeat the provisions of any`
  line `law, the transferee must hold the property for the benefit of the transferor.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (44086)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 86
  title `Bequest for illegal purpose.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44086&sectionno=85&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `Where a testator bequeaths certain property upon trust and`
  line `the purpose of the trust appears on the face of the will to be unlawful, or during the testators`
  line `lifetime the legatee agrees with him to apply the property for an unlawful purpose, the legatee`
  line `must hold the property for the benefit of the testators legal representative.`
  line
  line `Bequest of which revocation is prevented by coercion.-- Where property is bequeathed and the`
  line `revocation of the bequest is prevented by coercion, the legatee must hold the property for the benefit of`
  line `the testators legal representative.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (44311)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 87
  title `Transfer pursuant to rescindable contract.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44311&sectionno=86&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `Where property is transferred in pursuance of a`
  line `contract which is liable to rescission or induced by fraud or mistake, the transferee must, on receiving`
  line `notice to that effect, hold the property for the benefit of the transferor, subject to repayment by the latter`
  line `of the consideration actually paid.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (44312)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 88
  title `Debtor becoming creditor’s representative.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44312&sectionno=87&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `Where a debtor becomes the executor or other`
  line `legal representative of his creditor, he must hold the debt for the benefit of the persons interested therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (44313)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 89
  title `Advantage gained by fiduciary.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44313&sectionno=88&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `Where a trustee, executor, partner, agent, director of a`
  line `company, legal advisor, or other person bound in a fiduciary character to protect the interests of another`
  line `person, by availing himself of his character, gains for himself any pecuniary advantage, or where any`
  line `person so bound enters into any dealings under circumstances in which his own interests are, or may be,`
  line `adverse to those of such other person and thereby gains for himself a pecuniary advantage, he must hold`
  line `for the benefit of such other person the advantage so gained.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A, an executor, buys at an undervalue from B, a legatee, his claim under the will. B is ignorant of the value of the`
  line `bequest. A must hold for the benefit of B the difference between the price and value.`
  line
  line `(b) A, a trustee, uses the trust-property for the purpose of his own business. A holds for the benefit of his beneficiary the`
  line `profits arising from such user.`
  line
  line `(c) A, a trustee, retires from his trust in consideration of his successor paying him a sum of money. A holds such money for`
  line `the benefit of his beneficiary.`
  line
  line `(d) A, a partner, buys land in his own name with funds belonging to the partnership. A holds such land for the benefit of the`
  line partnership.
  line
  line `(e) A, a partner, employed on behalf of himself and his co-partners in negotiating the terms of a lease, clandestinely`
  line `stipulates with the lessor for payment to himself of a lakh of rupees. A holds the lakh for the benefit of the partnership.`
  line
  line `(f) A and B are partners. A dies. B, instead of winding up the affairs of the partnership, retains all the assets in the business.`
  line `B must account to As legal representative for the profits arising from As share of the capital.`
  line
  line `(g) A, an agent employed to obtain a lease for B, obtains the lease for himself. A holds the lease for the benefit of B.`
  line
  line `(h) A, a guardian, buys up for himself incumbrances on his ward Bs estate at an undervalue. A holds for the benefit of B the`
  line `incumbrances so bought, and can only charge him with what he has actually paid.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (44314)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 90
  title `Advantage gained by exercise of undue influence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44314&sectionno=89&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `Where, by the exercise of undue influence,`
  line `any advantage is gained in derogation of the interests of another, the person gaining such advantage`
  line `without consideration, or with notice that such influence has been exercised, must hold the advantage for`
  line `the benefit of the person whose interests have been so prejudiced.`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (44315)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 91
  title `Advantage gained by qualified owner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44315&sectionno=90&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `Where a tenant for life, co-owner, mortgagee or other`
  line `qualified owner of any property, by availing himself of his position as such, gains an advantage in`
  line `derogation of the rights of the other persons interested in the property, or where any such owner, as`
  line `representing all persons interested in such property, gains any advantage, he must hold, for the benefit of all persons so interested, the advantage so gained, but subject to repayment by such persons of their due`
  line `share of the expenses properly incurred, and to an indemnity by the same persons against liabilities`
  line `properly contracted, in gaining such advantage.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A, the tenant for life of leasehold property, renews the lease in his own name and for his own benefit. A holds the`
  line `renewed lease for the benefit of all those interested in the old lease.`
  line
  line `(b) A village belongs to a Hindu family. A, one of its members, pays nazrana to Government and thereby procures his`
  line `name to be entered as the inamdar of the village. A holds the village for the benefit of himself and the other members.`
  line
  line `(c) A mortgages land to B, who enters into possession. B allows the Government revenue to fall into arrear with a view to`
  line `the land being put up for sale and his becoming himself the purchaser of it. The land is accordingly sold to B. Subject to the`
  line `repayment of the amount due on the mortgage and of his expenses properly incurred as mortgagee, B holds the land for the`
  line `benefit of A.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (44316)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 92
  title `Property acquired with notice of existing contract`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44316&sectionno=91&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `Where a person acquires property`
  line `with notice that another person has entered into an existing contract affecting that property, of`
  line `which specific performance could be enforced, the former must hold the property for the benefit of`
  line `the latter to the extent necessary to give effect to the contract.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (44317)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 93
  title `Purchase by person contracting to buy property to be held on trust.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44317&sectionno=92&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `Where a person`
  line `contracts to buy property to be held on trust for certain beneficiaries and buys the property accordingly,`
  line `he must hold the property for their benefit to the extent necessary to give effect to the contract.`
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (44318)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 94
  title `Advantage secretly gained by one of several compounding creditors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725&sectionId=44318&sectionno=93&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00041_188202_1523272124725
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `Where creditors`
  line `compound the debts due to them, and one of such creditors, by a secret arrangement with the debtor, gains`
  line `an undue advantage over his co-creditors, he must hold for the benefit of such creditors the advantage so`
  line gained.
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
